  <h1>Contact Us</h1>

  <p>If you have any issues with Election Manager 2016 or want to contact us
  about it for any reason, please feel free to send us a note at

  { link_abs("mailto:support@lensflare.com", "support@lensflare.com") }.
  We're happy to hear from you, no matter if you've found a bug (we'd
  really like to fix those!), want to tell us what you think of the
  game (good or bad), or just have questions.</p>

  <p>You can also reach us at
  { link_abs("https://twitter.com/lensflare_games", "@lensflare_games") }
  on twitter.  Alternately, visit our page on
  { link_abs("http://www.facebook.com/lensflaregames", "Facebook") }.
  </p>

  <h1>Known Issues</h1>

  <ul>

    <li>Initial game loads with the historical 2012 scenario instead of 2016
    Clinton-Trump scenario [<em>workaround</em>: the 2016 scenario can be
    immediately loaded by using the load/generate button].</li>

  </ul>

  <p>The following is a list of bug fixes/new features from previous versions of
  Election Manager 2016:</p>

  <h1>v1.1.0 (currently available in the App Store)</h1>

  <ul>
    <li>Added 2016 scenarios with confirmed candidates.</li>
    <li>Additional portrait options.</li>
  </ul>

  <h1>v1.0.3</h1>

  <ul>
    <li><em>[iPad and iPhone only]</em> Fixed map market/state color
    picker not closing when turn ends/tab changed.</li>
    <li>Remember setup and randomness for scenarios on game setup
    screen.</li>
    <li>Additional background music.</li>
    <li>Minor cosmetic tweaks and fixes.</li>
  </ul>
</div>
